        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 12 at 6:32PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 631 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Westgate Park, or near
Athens, moving north at 25 mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Jefferson, Commerce, Athens, Maysville, Arcade, Nicholson, Bogart,
Ila, Athens-Clarke County, Westgate Park, James Holland Youth Sports
Cmpx, Pocataligo, Bear Creek Reservoir, Peach State Speedway,
Beechwood Hills, Sandy Creek Recreation Area, Oconee Heights,
Barretts Mill, State Botanical Garden Of Ga, and Apple Valley.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
